{"ts":"2026-06-27T08:26:06.755Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Improving Access Experience**\n\nI've homed in on the `PreviewRouteGuard` as the central point for access control. My focus has shifted toward enhancing the visual feedback and user experience surrounding role access within this guard. Currently, I'm reviewing the company's design constitution to identify relevant aesthetic themes to apply to the UX improvements. The key themes I see are Premium, Enterprise-grade, Expensive, Custom, Strategic, Modern, Calm, and Spacious.\n\n\n**Designing Interactive Security**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on the aesthetic design for the `!session` screen within `PreviewRouteGuard.tsx`. My goal is to make it interactive and stunning, consistent with our approved landing page theme. I'm brainstorming ideas like high-end SVG architecture graphics, animated holographic visuals, and futuristic \"Identity Decoupled\" messaging. I aim for a premium, custom, and interactive user experience.\n\n\n**Visualizing the Security**\n\nI'm now diving into the specifics of the aesthetic design. I'm leaning toward a \"Secure Enclave\" terminal vibe with motion elements, or beautiful SVG-based secure node visualizations, with a spacious, clean, premium editorial-style layout. I want a full-screen design, not the typical centered boxed card. I envision a left panel with an SVG visualization of the GFF AI Federated Security Architecture, and a right panel as an interactive \"Sandbox Simulation Controls\" dock. Alternatively, a unified widescreen layout with a \"Secured Network Node Map\" or \"Clearance Matrix Diagram\" using animated patterns seems promising. I'm focusing on interactive hover states, glassmorphism, glowing borders, and premium fonts.\n\n\n**Refining Boundary Aesthetics**\n\nI'm now shifting gears to the `!hasAccess` screen. It needs a significant visual overhaul. The current red-bordered card feels generic. My priority is a high-end aesthetic like a \"Clearance Boundary Access Log\" or an \"Active Firewall Inspection Console\". I'm envisioning an interactive SVG/CSS \"Access Control Matrix\" or \"Enclave Boundary Inspection Map\" that visually explains access restrictions in a clear, compelling way, to enhance the interactivity and strategic messaging.\n\n\n"}}
